Version 0.8 - July/31/2014

Software requirements

- Geant4 4.9.6.p02
- GDML 3.1.0 (Geant4 library)
- G4NDL 4.4 (Geant4 Data Source)
- ROOT
- Xerces 3.1.1 (GDML requirement)

*CMAKE file configured for compilation


Running the simulation

- Make sure the GDML model "Chamber.gdml" file is in the root of the executable.
- By default the simulation will create 1000 events using the macro [run_vis.mac]
- To run the default simulation with the chamber invisible, type: XenExe invisible
- To run a custom macro, type: XenExe [MACRO_FILE_NAME]


Notes

Color code for the particle tracking:
    - Electron: Red.
    - Proton: Blue.
    - Neutron: White.
    - Triton: Yellow.
    - Gamma: Green.


Future development

- Comparison of the asymmetry-pressure and gas percentage mix dependence.
- Variable neutron beam energy.


